## Checklists

### Before Starting Any Feature
- [ ] Read `.agents/learnings/` for relevant insights
- [ ] Check for similar existing features
- [ ] Review recent commits for patterns
- [ ] Create plan in `.agents/plans/`
- [ ] Define the first failing test or validation target
- [ ] Get plan approved before coding

### After Completing Any Feature
- [ ] Run the relevant multi-perspective assessment
- [ ] Document at least one learning
- [ ] Update rules if broadly applicable
- [ ] Confirm the intended tests pass

---

## Quick Reference

| Phase | Time | Key Activity |
|-------|------|--------------|
| **Plan** | 40% | Research → Document → Approve |
| **Work** | 10% | Execute plan with TDD where applicable |
| **Assess** | 30% | Multi-perspective review |
| **Compound** | 20% | Capture learnings, update rules |

---

## Key Principles

1. **Never code without a plan** - Quality is determined in planning
2. **Prefer test-first behavior changes** - Protect behavior before refactoring
3. **Always capture learnings** - Compounding only works if you document
4. **Read before you write** - Check learnings before building
5. **Small, frequent compounds** - Don't wait for big insights
6. **Make learnings searchable** - Tags, clear titles, organization
7. **Update rules when patterns emerge** - Seen twice = pattern
